manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: F225: Rockland Melbourne Hardside Expandable Spinner Wheel Luggage Set This expandable 2 piece set is made of polycarbonate. This material is extremely lightweight, durable, and protects the contents of your luggage. Multi-directional double spinner wheels rotate 360 degrees for easy maneuverability. This luggage allows you to pack more while avoiding the excess weight surcharges imposed by most airlines. 22"x 13"x 9" (with wheels) 28"x17"x12"

Telescoping Handle The telescoping handle stows away conveniently and allows for easy maneuvering when extended. Expandable The upright expands an extra 2 inches in depth to maximize your packing capacity. Double Spinner Wheels Double spinner wheels allow for durable 360 degree maneuverability wherever your travels take you.

About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If you want luggage that is used very little you will love these
reviews.reviewText: Love the bright colors and they are very light weight. Very easy to roll in all directions but I can tell they are not going to hold up well against the airline luggage carriers 😢

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Luggage set!
reviews.reviewText: This set was perfect for our weeklong cruise vacation. The bright colors made it so easy to spot in the baggage claim at the airport. I had several people tell me they loved this set. Rolled smoothly and the carryon was the perfect size for the overhead compartment. The expandable zipper was a nice feature when we returned home with extra items from the trip. Very good set of luggage and the price was great! Would definitely buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great price and I love the lime/green color!
reviews.reviewText: The only complaint I have is the pull up handle is flimsy. I will have to be careful not to break it. But, for the price, I am pleased.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars When it absolutely positively has to be there…
reviews.reviewText: Updated to add that the one of the wheels fell off on this luggage’s second trip due to the plastic completely breaking. I Travel a fair amount, and I have never had a suitcase fail within a year. while I love the colors, I do not recommend purchasing the suitcase, unless you’re not gonna be flying (and you don’t expect it to last long)… waiting for you at baggage claim.*Because NO ONE, and I mean NO ONE, is going to mistake your bag for their plain black suitcase!Checked zippers, wheels and handle thoroughly, all good! Durability remains to be seen, the case IS rather thin. Was pleasantly surprised both cases came covered in a thin film.I’m cautiously optimistic that I’ll be announcing my arrival in a uniquely blinding fashion for years to come!*Insincere apologies to FedEx for modifications to their slogan! 😉Edit 11/22 after first international trip; you can see if you smudge marks on the suitcase if you look really hard but that does not bother me at all. The suitcase made it out of the country and back in one solid piece and I couldn’t be happier with its maneuverability. Obviously the colors were a bonus when I was looking for it in customs! :-) great suitcase so far!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to Spot and Great Value
reviews.reviewText: I drove myself crazy before a week-long business trip across the country looking for suitable luggage sets that were also affordable. The ones I did find within my price range also had less-than-stellar reviews with handle problems, issues cracking and overall falling apart. I finally came across this set and saw that the reviews weren’t so bad and for the price I felt it was worth the risk.My experience with this set has been an overwhelmingly positive one. It has a couple of marks from the travel process but nothing that hinders it from doing it’s job. It is sleek and colorful, which I found great when trying to spot my bag at baggage claim. While others were arguing about their bags looking the same (just look at the tag) and someone else found his bag unable to zip up upon arrival, I quickly located mine and went about my business. The colors make it stand out like crazy, which I like. It expands which comes in handy when overpacking and overall functions as I would expect one of the higher priced ones to.I would definitely by again if my current set gets damaged to where it is unusable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great reasonably priced set
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for my 14yr old as her first luggage set. I didn't want to get anything too expensive but also wanted a hard set. She loves the color, it is just as it is in the pictures, very bright. We've only used the carry-on so far but will be cruising in a few months and she can't wait to use the large bag.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Looks great, easy to spot but doesn't seem reliable
reviews.reviewText: One of the wheels is missing after just 1 trip. I have other Rockland luggage sets that have lasted multiple trips and are still in a great shape. Can't say the same about this one though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Even better in person!
reviews.reviewText: These are great ! They roll very easily and the wheels are actually pretty high grade. The inside is nice and lined . The colors are really vibrant in person . I’m not sure how well it will hold up as far as dents and scratches, as I haven’t used them yet , but I feel it’s a great value for the price .
